{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"38739c42-9567-41a8-bd39-c9a6c0647c3b","content":"Use `dotnet test --hot-reload` — it watches for file changes and automatically re-runs affected tests:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hot-reload\n```\n\nThis is supported because your project uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (configured in `global.json`) with **MSTest 3.8.0** on .NET 10. The platform runner enables hot-reload natively.\n\nTo filter to just your failing test, combine with `--filter`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hot-reload --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nNow every time you save `InventoryServiceTests.cs` (or any source file), the runner will recompile and re-run that test automatically — no manual rebuild needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d73f0dbe-b236-4e56-92ce-a01fc5096179","outputTokens":177,"requestId":"4C30:2BC959:BD48E5:EBEB11:6A01328F"},"id":"45b2e48c-dcff-4383-9cbe-f304892077f7","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:36:20.518Z","parentId":"9b5bf417-45cb-4833-b9d3-22799228ca30"}
